#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6084
msgid "<b>Text editor</b> - A basic text editor to create and edit plain text files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6086
msgid "<b>Time sync</b> - Synchronizes the device time with NTP servers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6088
msgid ""
"<b>Tweak document settings</b> - Allows tweaking settings of a document "
"before it is loaded based on external factors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6090
msgid ""
"<b>Wallabag</b> - Downloads the latest articles from a Wallabag server as "
"individual EPUB files. Check our <a href= "
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/Wallabag\">wiki page</a> for "
"more info."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6094
msgid "Controlling your reader from another device - HTTP Inspector Plugin"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6097
msgid ""
"This plugin allows you to control your device from another device over "
"wifi. It works by running a simple HTTP server on your device which serves a "
"page containing KOReader controls. You can access this page over your "
"network and control your reader device.  But be aware of these points when "
"using this plugin:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6103
msgid "This is an experimental plugin so <b>use this at your own risk</b>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6105
msgid ""
"This plugin is enabled by default, but the server is <b>NOT</b> started by "
"default. You can start it manually or set it to <b>auto start</b>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6108
msgid ""
"You should run this plugin <b>only on trusted networks</b>, as it is highly "
"insecure (no HTTPS, no access restriction, no authentication)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6112
msgid ""
"You can read an example use case for this plugin on the <a href= "
"\"https://www.mobileread.com/forums/showthread.php?t=359837\">MobileRead "
"forum</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6115
msgid "User patches"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6117
msgid ""
"User patches are small files written in <b>Lua</b> language.  They can "
"change the functionality of KOReader without modifying your installation "
"permanently. They can be written by developers, other users or you can write "
"one yourself (if you have the necessary extensive knowledge about the "
"KOReader internals)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6122
msgid ""
"You can find a current list of <span class=\"ui\">User patches</span> in our "
"<a href= \"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/wiki/User-patches\">wiki</a> "
"and in the <b>GitHub issues list</b> marked with the <span class= "
"\"ui\">User patch available</span> tag. You can see them by following this "
"<a href= "
"\"https://github.com/koreader/koreader/issues?q=+label%3A%22User+patch+available%22\"> "
"link</a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6130
msgid "Basic usage ‚Äì Adding an already written patch to your KOReader:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ol><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6133
msgid ""
"Create a directory named <span class=\"ui\">patches</span> under <span "
"class=\"ui\">koreader directory</span> on your device (On Android this "
"folder is located on the SD-card)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ol><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6136
msgid ""
"Download and put the patch file with <b>.lua</b> extension in this <span "
"class=\"ui\">patches</span> directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6140
msgid "Patch manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6141
msgid ""
"When you create a patches directory as instructed, a new plugin named <span "
"class=\"ui\">Patch Management</span> becomes available in the plugins menu "
"after restarting KOReader. With this plugin you can see the list and status "
"of your user patches and enable/disable them. You can tap <span "
"class=\"ui\">About patch manager</span> menu item to see more info."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6147
msgid "Naming the patch"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6148
msgid ""
"Execution order of a patch is determined by the first digit of the number in "
"the patch name. For example: <span class= "
"\"ui\">2-TOC-title-patch.lua</span> If there are several patches starting "
"with the same digit, the execution order is the natural order "
"<b>(1&lt;10&lt;11&lt;12&lt;13&lt;‚Ä¶&lt;109&lt;‚Ä¶&lt;10010)</b>.  If you are "
"just downloading an already made patch you don‚Äôt need to change the file "
"name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6155
msgid "Names starting with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6157
msgid "<b>0</b> - Executed very early and only once after an update"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6159
msgid ""
"<b>1</b> - Excuted very early on every start of KOReader (but after 0 if "
"applicable)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6161
msgid ""
"<b>2</b> - Executed after <span class=\"ui\">UIManager</span> is ready on "
"every start of KOReader"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6163
msgid "<b>3-7</b> - Reserved"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6164
msgid "<b>8</b> - Executed before exit and before settings get saved"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ul><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6166
msgid "<b>9</b> - Executed right before exit"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6168
msgid ""
"If you have a problem with a user patch, you can revert to your previous "
"configuration by removing the patch file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6171
msgid "TIPS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6172
msgid "Reading Tips"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6173
msgid "Switching between documents quickly"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6175
msgid ""
"If you need to switch between two documents (when comparing them for "
"example), there is a quicker way than going through the <span "
"class=\"ui\">File Browser</span>. KOReader can open the last document with a "
"gesture (<b><span style= \"font-family: microns;\">ÓúÄÓúÅÓúÄ</span> "
"multiswipe</b>). If you define a gesture‚Äôs action as <span class=\"ui\">Open "
"previous document</span>, you can switch between two documents quickly "
"similar to the <b>Alt+Tab</b> feature on the desktop computers. You can find "
"this feature under:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6185
msgid ""
"/ Taps and gestures / Gesture manager / ‚ÄúANY GESTURE‚Äù / General / Open "
"Previous Document"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6188
msgid ""
"Also you can use the <span class=\"ui\">History</span> dialog to switch "
"between documents quickly. The history screen can be opened with the <span "
"style=\"font-family: microns;\">ÓúÅÓúÇ</span> multiswipe gesture. You can also "
"define any other gesture for this of course."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6193
msgid "Changing your book cover"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6194
msgid "You can change your book cover from this menu:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6196
msgid "/ Book information /"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6198
msgid "/ Set cover image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6200
msgid "Custom book cover from a screenshot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6202
msgid ""
"Some books don‚Äôt come with proper book covers. Or they may have their cover "
"on the second page so it doesn‚Äôt show up properly. Or maybe the cover is not "
"suitable for e-ink (too light or dark). Or you prefer to set some image from "
"the book as cover."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6206
msgid ""
"In situations like this you can quickly take a screenshot and set it as the "
"current book‚Äôs cover. Screenshot gesture is a <b>long diagonal swipe</b> by "
"default. Also <b>touching opposing diagonal corners</b> will take a "
"screenshot. You can use this second shortcut when viewing an image. After "
"taking your screenshot you can select <span class=\"ui\">Set as book "
"cover</span> from the dialog."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6213
msgid "You can remove this custom book cover here:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6215 user_guide/en.html:6293
msgid "/ Book information"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6217
msgid ""
"On the book information page, long-press on the <span class= \"ui\">Cover "
"image</span> item and then select <span class=\"ui\">Reset custom</span>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6220
msgid ""
"You can also reset the book cover with the <span class= \"ui\">Reset</span> "
"dialog, which you can access by long-pressing the filename in the <span "
"class=\"ui\">File Browser</span>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6223
msgid ""
"<span class=\"label_red\">WARNING</span> Be very careful when using this "
"<span class=\"ui\">Reset</span> dialog and be sure that only <span "
"class=\"ui\">Custom cover image</span> item is checked otherwise you can "
"reset everything related to your book accidentally."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6228
msgid "Avoiding opening links accidentally"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6230
msgid ""
"If your document has links and you are accidentally tapping them while "
"turning the page or using other gestures, you can turn off <span "
"class=\"ui\">Following links by tapping</span> via this menu item:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6235
msgid "/ Taps and Gestures / Links / Tap to follow links"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6237
msgid ""
"After disabling this setting, to follow a link you have to long-tap on it "
"and select <span class=\"ui\">Follow link</span> from the popup menu. If you "
"have the opposite problem and you want to make tapping links easier, you can "
"enable <span class=\"ui\">Allow larger tap area around links</span> from the "
"same menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6242
msgid "Reading statistics after midnight"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6244
msgid ""
"In reading statistics you can change the start of day used for "
"calculations. This is useful if you are reading after midnight for example "
"and want your reading session counted as today instead of the next day. This "
"applies only to the <span class=\"ui\">Day timeline view</span> and "
"optionally to the <span class= \"ui\">Calendar view</span>; it does not "
"apply to any of the other statistics reports. You can set this time at:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6252
msgid "/ Reading statistics / Settings / Daily timeline starts at..."
msgstr ""

