msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6255
msgid "Updating KOReader"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6256
msgid ""
"KOReader can update itself over Wi-Fi. You can trigger the check via this "
"menu item:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6259
msgid "/ Update / Check for update"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6261
msgid "Adding a password lock to KOReader"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6263
msgid ""
"We don't have a direct option for this in KOReader. But there is a "
"workaround to achieve this kind of lock screen functionality. You can set up "
"KOReader to keep the screensaver on the screen until you enter a chosen "
"gesture. To achieve this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ol><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6268
msgid ""
"Choose any gesture (including the complex ones with custom multiswipes) and "
"make it your <b>\"unlock\"</b> gesture by going to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ol><li><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6271
msgid ""
"/ Taps and gestures / Gesture manager / \"your selected gesture\" / Device / "
"Exit screensaver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ol><li>
#: user_guide/en.html:6275
msgid "And then enable this option:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><ol><li><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6277
msgid ""
"/ Screen / Screensaver / Settings / Keep the screensaver on screen after "
"wakeup / Until 'Exit screensaver' gesture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6282
msgid "Automatic screen dimming"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6283
msgid ""
"KOReader can dim your frontlight to preserve battery if your device is idle "
"for a while. You can turn on and adjust this feature via:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6287
msgid "/ Screen / Automatic dimmer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div>
#: user_guide/en.html:6289
msgid "Line/word count of a page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><p>
#: user_guide/en.html:6290
msgid ""
"If you want to know how many lines or words are being shown on the current "
"page you can see it at:"
